{"type":"message","id":"f14049b3","parentId":"2c23bc91","timestamp":"2026-03-31T08:05:53.605Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nNo, I don't have an \"auto mode\" like Claude Code's agentic mode where it autonomously runs commands, edits files, and iterates without asking.\n\nWhat I *do* have is close though:\n\n- **Sub-agents** — I can spawn isolated sessions that run tasks end-to-end and report back when done\n- **Cron jobs** — scheduled tasks that run autonomously on a timer\n- **Heartbeats** — periodic check-ins where I can do background work\n- **ACP sessions** — I can spin up Codex/Claude Code as a coding agent that works autonomously on a task\n\nSo if you need something done hands-off, I can either:\n1. **Spawn a sub-agent** with a clear task → it runs, finishes, reports back\n2. **Launch a Codex/Claude Code session** for coding tasks → it works autonomously in a sandbox\n\nWhat are you trying to do? I can probably set it up to run without you babysitting it."}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":230,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":26953,"totalTokens":27186,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.00575,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.16845625,"total":0.17422125}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774944307924}}
