{"type":"message","id":"285677a3","parentId":"f7bdf01b","timestamp":"2026-03-31T08:15:54.264Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\nSystem: [2026-03-31 08:06:36 UTC] Exec completed (grand-em, code 0) :: t-support.html /home/openclaw/council-room/frontend/romebois/index.html /home/openclaw/council-room/frontend/clear.html /home/openclaw/council-room/frontend/projects.html /home/op…\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"AC674F472DDFD348AA54172D6CBF13BD\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"+6285133221170\",\n  \"sender\": \"Richard Chandra Tjiang\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Richard Chandra Tjiang (+6285133221170)\",\n  \"id\": \"+6285133221170\",\n  \"name\": \"Richard Chandra Tjiang\",\n  \"e164\": \"+6285133221170\"\n}\n```\n\nexplain auto mode and how it's different to what we have"}],"timestamp":1774944954242}}
{"type":"message","id":"425f76b5","parentId":"285677a3","timestamp":"2026-03-31T08:16:08.506Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nClaude Code's \"Auto Mode\" = you give it a task and it runs autonomously — executes commands, edits files, installs packages, runs tests, iterates on errors — all without asking permission at each step. You just watch it work.\n\n**What we have that's similar:**\n- **Sub-agents** — I spawn an isolated session with a task, it runs end-to-end, reports when done. Basically the same idea, but it's a separate session, not me visually doing things in front of you.\n- **ACP sessions** — I can literally launch Claude Code / Codex as a coding agent. That *is* auto mode, just running through OpenClaw.\n\n**What's different:**\n- Claude Code's auto mode is one agent in one terminal, you see every action live\n- Ours is more like a dispatcher model — I can run *multiple* sub-agents in parallel on different tasks, but the visibility is less \"watch me type in real-time\" and more \"I'll tell you when it's done\"\n\n**The gap:**\nWe don't have a mode where I autonomously chain 10+ tool calls in a row without any back-and-forth in *this* chat. I still operate in a request-response pattern. If you say \"build X,\" I'll do several steps but I'm not going to silently run 50 commands and come back 10 minutes later with a finished product — I'd break it into chunks or spawn a sub-agent for that.\n\n**TL;DR:** We have the capability (sub-agents + ACP), just packaged differently. Claude Code = one agent, live terminal. Us = orchestrator that can dispatch multiple autonomous workers. Trade-off: less live visibility, more parallelism.\n\nWant me to set up something specific in auto-mode style? I can spawn a sub-agent for any task and it'll run hands-off."}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":425,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":65855,"totalTokens":66283,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.010625,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.41159375000000004,"total":0.42223375}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774944954256}}
{"type":"message","id":"a35a805f","parentId":"425f76b5","timestamp":"2026-03-31T08:16:09.097Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude Code's \"Auto Mode\" = you give it a task and it runs autonomously — executes commands, edits files, installs packages, runs tests, iterates on errors — all without asking permission at each step. You just watch it work.\n\n**What we have that's similar:**\n- **Sub-agents** — I spawn an isolated session with a task, it runs end-to-end, reports when done. Basically the same idea, but it's a separate session, not me visually doing things in front of you.\n- **ACP sessions** — I can literally launch Claude Code / Codex as a coding agent. That *is* auto mode, just running through OpenClaw.\n\n**What's different:**\n- Claude Code's auto mode is one agent in one terminal, you see every action live\n- Ours is more like a dispatcher model — I can run *multiple* sub-agents in parallel on different tasks, but the visibility is less \"watch me type in real-time\" and more \"I'll tell you when it's done\"\n\n**The gap:**\nWe don't have a mode where I autonomously chain 10+ tool calls in a row without any back-and-forth in *this* chat. I still operate in a request-response pattern. If you say \"build X,\" I'll do several steps but I'm not going to silently run 50 commands and come back 10 minutes later with a finished product — I'd break it into chunks or spawn a sub-agent for that.\n\n**TL;DR:** We have the capability (sub-agents + ACP), just packaged differently. Claude Code = one agent, live terminal. Us = orchestrator that can dispatch multiple autonomous workers. Trade-off: less live visibility, more parallelism.\n\nWant me to set up something specific in auto-mode style? I can spawn a sub-agent for any task and it'll run hands-off."}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774944969092}}
