{"type":"message","id":"f3a0bb8f","parentId":"6f1d16cc","timestamp":"2026-03-31T13:19:16.924Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nOke, gw gas semua sekaligus. Biar efisien gw dispatch parallel:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_DjzOwg4E7kpahb6QxUJCbv","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"agentId":"uriel","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":600,"task":"Build a Message Forwarding Rules system for OpenClaw WhatsApp.\n\n**Context:**\n- OpenClaw workspace: /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace\n- MAGI v2 settings: /home/openclaw/magi-v2/frontend/settings/index.html\n- MAGI v2 backend: /home/openclaw/magi-v2/backend/server.js\n- Contact metadata: /home/openclaw/.openclaw/wa-contacts.json\n\n**What to build:**\n\n### 1. Rules Storage\nCreate /home/openclaw/.openclaw/wa-forward-rules.json:\n```json\n[\n  {\"from\": \"+6285161502503\", \"action\": \"forward\", \"to\": \"+6285133221170\", \"label\": \"Forward Kenny → Lucy\"},\n  {\"from\": \"+6281345985715\", \"action\": \"forward_summarize\", \"to\": \"+6285133221170\", \"label\": \"Forward+Summarize Ceka → Lucy\"}\n]\n```\n\nActions: \"forward\" (relay message as-is), \"forward_summarize\" (relay + add AI summary), \"notify\" (just tell Lucy someone messaged)\n\n### 2. Backend API (add to server.js)\n- GET /wa-forward-rules → list all rules\n- POST /wa-forward-rules → add rule {from, action, to, label}\n- DELETE /wa-forward-rules → remove rule {id or index}\n- PUT /wa-forward-rules → update rule\n\n### 3. Frontend (add card to settings/index.html)\nAdd a \"Message Forwarding Rules\" card in settings:\n- Show existing rules with from/to contact names (lookup from wa-contacts.json)\n- Action type badge (forward=blue, forward_summarize=purple, notify=yellow)\n- Add form: select \"from\" contact, select action type, select \"to\" contact\n- Delete button per rule\n- Place after WhatsApp Allowlist card\n\nMatch existing MAGI v2 style. Restart pm2 magi-v2 when done."}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_8vAMAohCuYsXObwSpJEst0","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"agentId":"rafael","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":600,"task":"Build a Personal Knowledge Base system that auto-saves research results.\n\n**Context:**\n- Workspace: /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace\n- Research results from sub-agents get stored here for instant recall\n\n**What to build:**\n\n### 1. Knowledge Base Storage\nCreate directory: /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/knowledge-base/\nCreate index file: /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/knowledge-base/index.json\n\nStructure:\n```json\n{\n  \"entries\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"uuid\",\n      \"title\": \"Hitam Manis Cafe Balikpapan\",\n      \"category\": \"research\",\n      \"tags\": [\"cafe\", \"balikpapan\", \"food\"],\n      \"summary\": \"Short summary...\",\n      \"content_file\": \"hitam-manis-cafe.md\",\n      \"created\": \"2026-03-31T08:30:00Z\",\n      \"source\": \"metis-research\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Save existing research\nSave the two research results we already have as markdown files:\n- knowledge-base/hitam-manis-cafe-balikpapan.md (search workspace for the research content about Hitam Manis Cafe)\n- knowledge-base/28-coffee-balikpapan.md (search for 28 Coffee research)\nAdd them to index.json with proper metadata.\n\n### 3. Create a helper script\nCreate /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/knowledge-base/save-research.sh that:\n- Takes title, category, tags, content as arguments\n- Generates a slug filename\n- Saves content as .md file\n- Updates index.json\n- Usage: ./save-research.sh \"Title\" \"category\" \"tag1,tag2\" \"content...\"\n\n### 4. MAGI v2 Integration\nAdd to MAGI v2 backend (/home/openclaw/magi-v2/backend/server.js):\n- GET /knowledge-base → list all entries (from index.json)\n- GET /knowledge-base/:id → get full content\n- POST /knowledge-base → save new entry\n- DELETE /knowledge-base/:id → delete entry\n\nAdd a simple \"Knowledge Base\" page to MAGI v2 frontend:\nCreate /home/openclaw/magi-v2/frontend/knowledge/index.html:\n- List all saved research/knowledge entries\n- Search/filter by title, tags, category\n- Click to view full content\n- Clean card-based layout matching MAGI v2 style\n\nAlso add a link to the knowledge base in the MAGI v2 dashboard (/home/openclaw/magi-v2/frontend/dashboard/index.html) — add it as a new app card.\n\nRestart pm2 magi-v2 when done."}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_vI4IBuZLOYqUBsn2yw334j","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"agentId":"samael","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":600,"task":"Build a Smart Notifications system using OpenClaw cron jobs and HEARTBEAT.md.\n\n**Context:**\n- Workspace: /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace\n- HEARTBEAT.md: /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n- Lucy's timezone: Asia/Makassar (UTC+8 / WITA)\n- Lucy's WhatsApp: +6285133221170\n\n**What to build:**\n\n### 1. Update HEARTBEAT.md\nReplace the current empty HEARTBEAT.md with a smart notification checklist:\n\n```markdown\n# HEARTBEAT.md — Smart Notifications\n\n## Checks (rotate through, 2-4x per day)\n1. Weather check for Balikpapan — if rain expected, notify Lucy\n2. Check if any cron jobs failed recently\n3. Check server health (disk space, memory, PM2 processes)\n\n## Rules\n- Quiet hours: 23:00-07:00 WITA (15:00-23:00 UTC) — only urgent\n- If nothing interesting, reply HEARTBEAT_OK\n- Don't repeat notifications within 4 hours\n- Track last check times in memory/heartbeat-state.json\n```\n\n### 2. Create heartbeat state tracker\nCreate /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/heartbeat-state.json:\n```json\n{\n  \"lastChecks\": {\n    \"weather\": null,\n    \"server_health\": null,\n    \"cron_status\": null\n  },\n  \"lastNotification\": null,\n  \"quietHoursStart\": \"23:00\",\n  \"quietHoursEnd\": \"07:00\",\n  \"timezone\": \"Asia/Makassar\"\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Create cron jobs for scheduled reports\nUse the cron tool format to document (in a file) what cron jobs should be set up:\n\nCreate /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/cron-setup.md with recommended crons:\n\n1. **Daily Morning Brief** (8:00 AM WITA / 00:00 UTC daily)\n   - Summary of yesterday's agent activity\n   - Any pending tasks\n   - Weather for the day\n   \n2. **Weekly Review** (Sunday 8 PM WITA / 12:00 UTC)\n   - What was accomplished this week\n   - Agent usage/costs estimate\n   - Next week priorities\n\n3. **Server Health Check** (every 6 hours)\n   - Disk space, memory, PM2 status\n   - Alert if anything critical\n\nDocument the exact cron job configs (schedule, payload, sessionTarget) ready to be added.\n\n### 4. Template Responses\nCreate /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/templates/responses.json:\n```json\n{\n  \"templates\": [\n    {\"id\": \"busy\", \"trigger\": \"busy|sibuk\", \"response\": \"Lucy lagi sibuk, nanti di-reply ya 👍\"},\n    {\"id\": \"location\", \"trigger\": \"dimana|where\", \"response\": \"Lucy lagi di Balikpapan\"},\n    {\"id\": \"acknowledge\", \"trigger\": \"noted|ok|oke\", \"response\": \"Noted, udah gw sampaikan ke Lucy ✅\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThis is for reference — the actual routing logic is handled by Michael (main agent) reading these templates.\n\nMake sure all files are created and properly formatted. Don't actually create the cron jobs — just document them in cron-setup.md for Lucy to review and approve."}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":2306,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":135698,"totalTokens":138007,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.05765,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.8481125,"total":0.9057775}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774963109194}}
