{"type":"message","id":"ddd68217","parentId":"dc28beed","timestamp":"2026-03-31T13:34:30.446Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_LfiH8dUBcQjHGpXUiKxKJS","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"agentId":"uriel","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":600,"task":"Build Phase 1 of a D&D 2024 Web App. This is for a private angkringan (casual cafe) D&D group in Balikpapan. Desktop-first, PIN-based auth.\n\n**Host it at:** /home/openclaw/dnd-app/\n- Frontend: /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/\n- Backend: /home/openclaw/dnd-app/backend/\n\n**Reference doc:** /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/dnd-2024-reference.md (read this first for D&D 2024 rules)\n\n**Phase 1 — Build these features:**\n\n### 1. Backend (Node.js + Express or Fastify)\n- Port: 3004\n- WebSocket for real-time sync (dice rolls, initiative, etc.)\n- JSON file storage (no database needed): /home/openclaw/dnd-app/data/\n- Auth: simple PIN system\n\n### 2. PIN-Based Auth & Rooms\n- DM creates a room → gets a 6-digit PIN\n- Players join with PIN\n- Each player picks/creates a character name\n- DM has special controls (initiative, session management)\n- Store rooms in /home/openclaw/dnd-app/data/rooms.json\n- Store characters in /home/openclaw/dnd-app/data/characters.json\n\n### 3. Character Sheet Builder (D&D 2024)\nBased on the reference doc, create a character builder with:\n- **Species** (10): Aasimar, Dragonborn, Dwarf, Elf, Gnome, Goliath, Halfling, Human, Orc, Tiefling\n- **Classes** (12): Barbarian, Bard, Cleric, Druid, Fighter, Monk, Paladin, Ranger, Rogue, Sorcerer, Warlock, Wizard\n- **Backgrounds** (16): Acolyte, Artisan, Charlatan, Criminal, Entertainer, Farmer, Guard, Guide, Hermit, Merchant, Noble, Sage, Sailor, Scribe, Soldier, Wayfarer\n- **Ability Scores**: Standard Array (15,14,13,12,10,8), Point Buy, or Manual entry\n- **Background gives**: +2/+1 ability scores + Origin Feat\n- **Auto-calculate**: HP, AC, proficiency bonus, saving throws, skill modifiers\n- **Level**: 1-20, auto-update proficiency bonus\n- **Spell slots** per class/level\n- Editable fields, auto-save\n\n### 4. Dice Roller (Real-time Shared)\n- Dice types: d4, d6, d8, d10, d12, d20, d100\n- Roll multiple dice (e.g. 2d6+3)\n- Advantage/Disadvantage for d20\n- Results broadcast to ALL players in room via WebSocket\n- Roll history log (who rolled what, when)\n- Dice animation (simple CSS animation, nothing fancy)\n\n### 5. Initiative Tracker\n- DM adds combatants (players auto-populate, DM adds monsters manually)\n- Roll initiative (d20 + DEX mod) or manual entry\n- Auto-sort by initiative\n- \"Next Turn\" button (DM only)\n- Current turn highlighted\n- HP tracker per combatant (DM can adjust)\n- Conditions dropdown (Blinded, Charmed, Prone, etc.)\n- Remove combatant\n\n### 6. GM Session Summary\n- DM has a \"Session Notes\" panel\n- Can type freeform notes during the session\n- \"AI Summary\" button — sends the session notes + dice roll history + combat log to AI, gets a structured summary:\n  - What happened this session\n  - Key decisions made\n  - Combat outcomes\n  - Loot gained\n  - XP/milestones\n  - Cliffhanger/next session hook\n- Summary saved per session, viewable in history\n- For the AI summary, POST to http://127.0.0.1:3001/voice/chat with {agentId: \"sarael\", message: \"Summarize this D&D session: [notes + logs]\"}\n\n### 7. UI Design\n- **Desktop-first**, dark theme matching the D&D vibe\n- Color scheme: deep dark (#0a0e1a base), gold accents (#F59E0B), red for damage (#EF4444), green for healing (#10B981)\n- Fantasy-inspired but clean/modern (not medieval clipart)\n- Google Fonts: Inter for UI, Cinzel for headers (fantasy feel)\n- Layout: sidebar (navigation) + main content area\n- Tabs: Character Sheet | Dice | Initiative | Spells | Session Notes\n- Mobile-responsive but optimized for desktop\n\n### 8. Spell Book (Basic)\n- Searchable list of spells organized by level (0-9)\n- Filter by class (which classes can cast it)\n- Spell card shows: name, level, school, casting time, range, components, duration, description\n- For MVP: include at least all cantrips and level 1-3 spells (hardcode the data, can expand later)\n- Player can mark \"prepared spells\" based on their class\n- Spell slot tracker (checkboxes per level)\n\n### 9. PM2 & Caddy Setup\n- Register with pm2: pm2 start backend/server.js --name dnd-app\n- pm2 save\n- Add Caddy route to /etc/caddy/Caddyfile:\n```\n@dnd path /dnd /dnd/*\nhandle @dnd {\n    uri strip_prefix /dnd\n    root * /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend\n    try_files {path} {path}/index.html /index.html\n    file_server\n    header Cache-Control \"no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate\"\n}\n\n@dndapi path /dnd-api /dnd-api/*\nhandle @dndapi {\n    uri strip_prefix /dnd-api\n    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:3004\n}\n\n@dndws path /dnd-ws /dnd-ws/*\nhandle @dndws {\n    uri strip_prefix /dnd-ws\n    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:3004\n}\n```\n- sudo systemctl reload caddy\n\n**IMPORTANT:**\n- This is a BIG build. Focus on getting the structure right and all features working.\n- Use a single index.html with tab-based navigation (SPA style) for the frontend\n- Spell data can be a large JS object/file embedded or loaded from a JSON endpoint\n- The character sheet should auto-calculate everything based on class/level/ability scores\n- Make it FUN to use — this is for a D&D night at an angkringan!"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":1745,"cacheRead":147866,"cacheWrite":620,"totalTokens":150234,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.043625000000000004,"cacheRead":0.073933,"cacheWrite":0.003875,"total":0.12144800000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774964029937}}
