{"type":"message","id":"cb6b8914","parentId":"6e4539f5","timestamp":"2026-03-31T14:32:26.736Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHaha bener juga, gw dispatch Uriel aja buat fix semua mobile issues sekaligus. Lebih bersih daripada gw tambal satu-satu:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_47M577LQVuGva7Zzyua5f5","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"agentId":"uriel","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":600,"task":"Fix ALL mobile issues in Paul Simulator (D&D web app). The app works fine on desktop but is broken on mobile.\n\n**Files:**\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/index.html\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/styles.css\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/app.js\n\nRead all files first. Test by checking layout at 375px viewport width.\n\n**Known mobile bugs to fix:**\n\n### 1. Hamburger menu (☰) overlaps heading text\nThe ☰ button is position:fixed at top:10px left:10px, but it overlaps the page heading (\"SESSION NOTES\", \"MANAGE PLAYERS\", etc.). The heading text gets cut off behind the hamburger.\n- Fix: Add proper padding-top to main content when hamburger is visible, OR move the hamburger into a proper mobile header bar.\n\n### 2. \"Save to Obsidian\" button text gets cut off\nThe three buttons (Save Notes, AI Summary, Save to Obsidian) overflow on mobile. \"Save to Obsid...\" gets cut off.\n- Fix: Stack buttons vertically on mobile, or make text smaller, or use icons only on mobile.\n\n### 3. Input fields for adding players are too small\nThe input field next to \"+ Add\" / \"+ Add Player\" button appears tiny on mobile.\n- Fix: Make the add-player-row stack vertically on mobile (input full width on top, button full width below).\n\n### 4. Text input RTL reversal bug\nWhen typing in input fields on mobile, text appears reversed (e.g., \"Angel\" becomes \"legnA\"). This is caused by CSS `unicode-bidi: bidi-override` which was added as a fix but actually causes the problem on some mobile browsers.\n- Fix: REMOVE all `unicode-bidi` and `direction` CSS overrides. Instead, add `dir=\"ltr\"` attribute directly on each input element in the HTML. This is the correct HTML-level fix that works on all browsers.\n\n### 5. General mobile layout overflow\nContent overflows horizontally on mobile (you can scroll right and see empty space).\n- Fix: Add `overflow-x: hidden` on body and main containers. Ensure no element has fixed widths wider than viewport.\n\n### 6. Sidebar navigation on mobile\nThe sidebar is hidden off-screen with the hamburger toggle. This works but:\n- Needs a proper overlay when open (darken background)\n- Sidebar should close when a nav item is clicked\n- Add smooth transition\n\n### 7. Dice section on mobile\n- Dice buttons should be in a grid that fits the screen (4 columns max)\n- Dice tray should be compact\n- Quick roll presets should scroll horizontally\n\n### What to do:\n1. Create a proper mobile header bar (hidden on desktop, shown on mobile) with hamburger + current page title\n2. Fix ALL input elements — remove CSS direction hacks, use HTML dir=\"ltr\" attribute instead\n3. Fix all button rows to wrap/stack on mobile\n4. Fix content padding so nothing overlaps with mobile header\n5. Test every tab on mobile viewport: Login, Manage Players, Character Sheet, Dice, Initiative, Spells, Session Notes\n6. Make sure the app is fully usable on a 375px wide screen\n\n**Also fix stored data:**\nRun this to fix reversed names in the database:\n```js\n// In server.js or as a one-time script, check all room player names for reversed text\n```\nActually just check /home/openclaw/dnd-app/data/rooms.json and fix any reversed names manually.\n\npm2 restart dnd-app when done."}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":1003,"cacheRead":25861,"cacheWrite":209959,"totalTokens":236826,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.025075,"cacheRead":0.0129305,"cacheWrite":1.3122437500000002,"total":1