{"type":"message","id":"2679fe28","parentId":"00becca2","timestamp":"2026-03-31T19:07:35.147Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nDari list tadi yang belum dibikin:\n\n**⚔️ Combat & Gameplay:**\n3. **Loot Generator** — habis combat, random treasure table berdasarkan CR\n4. **Combat Simulator** — DM test encounter balance sebelum session\n\n**🎭 Roleplay & Story:**\n5. **Character Journal** — player tulis diary in-character, AI bantu generate entries\n6. **NPC Voice Chat** — AI generate suara unik per NPC (TTS)\n\n**📊 Meta & Engagement:**\n7. **Campaign Dashboard** — timeline, character progression, total nat 20s, most damage\n8. **Achievement System** — badges: \"First Blood\", \"Nat 20 Streak\", \"Dragon Slayer\"\n\n**🎲 Fun & Social:**\n9. **Tavern Mini-Games** — card games, dice gambling buat downtime\n10. **AI Dungeon Master** — full AI DM mode buat solo play\n\n**Bonus ide baru:**\n11. **Encounter Builder** — DM pilih monsters, system auto-calculate difficulty (Easy/Medium/Hard/Deadly) berdasarkan party level\n12. **Condition & Buff Tracker** — visual cards buat track semua active effects per character (concentration spells, temp HP, potion timers)\n13. **Music/Ambiance Player** — DM set mood music per scene (tavern, combat, dungeon, forest) pake embedded ambient sounds\n14. **Character Relationship Map** — visual graph siapa kenal siapa, alliances, rivalries\n\nKalau gw recommend priority:\n- **Loot Generator** (quick win, useful every session)\n- **Achievement System** (bikin player excited)\n- **AI Dungeon Master** (game changer buat solo/no-DM sessions)\n\nMau yang mana?"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":444,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":388346,"totalTokens":388793,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.0111,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":2.4271625,"total":2.4382775000000003}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774984017630}}
{"type":"message","id":"56b265a5","parentId":"2679fe28","timestamp":"2026-03-31T19:08:53.810Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"ACC0E678603534F122E3E01345C9F635\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"+6285133221170\",\n  \"sender\": \"Richard Chandra Tjiang\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Richard Chandra Tjiang (+6285133221170)\",\n  \"id\": \"+6285133221170\",\n  \"name\": \"Richard Chandra Tjiang\",\n  \"e164\": \"+6285133221170\"\n}\n```\n\nselain Music Ambiance Tracker semuanya bagus, dan 1 lagi, player bisa upload gambar sebagai avatar"}],"timestamp":1774984133775}}
{"type":"message","id":"6c7aadd7","parentId":"56b265a5","timestamp":"2026-03-31T19:09:58.569Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGas semua sekaligus. Gw dispatch parallel:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_jEHU07YUWgguqDG0W4Dkk3","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"agentId":"uriel","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":600,"task":"Add these features to Paul Simulator (D&D web app). Read all existing files first.\n\n**Files:**\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/index.html\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/app.js\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/styles.css\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/backend/server.js\n\n## Feature 1: Loot Generator\nDM-only feature in initiative/combat tab area.\n\n- \"🎁 Generate Loot\" button in initiative tracker section (after combat)\n- Input: CR of encounter (dropdown 0-20), loot type (Individual/Hoard)\n- Random loot table based on CR:\n  - CR 0-4: copper/silver, common items\n  - CR 5-10: gold, uncommon magic items\n  - CR 11-16: gold/platinum, rare items\n  - CR 17+: platinum, very rare/legendary items\n- Generate: random gold amount + random items from tables\n- Include classic D&D items: Potion of Healing, +1 weapons, Bag of Holding, Cloak of Elvenkind, etc.\n- Hardcode ~50 magic items across rarities\n- Result shows as a styled \"treasure chest\" card\n- DM can share loot to players (broadcast via WebSocket)\n\n## Feature 2: Achievement System\nTracked per player, visible to everyone.\n\n- Backend: store achievements in character data or separate file\n- Track these events automatically:\n  - \"First Blood\" — first damage dealt\n  - \"Natural Born\" — first Nat 20\n  - \"Fumble King\" — first Nat 1\n  - \"Dice Addict\" — 100 dice rolled\n  - \"Critical Streak\" — 2 Nat 20s in a row\n  - \"Survivor\" — survived a death save\n  - \"Big Hitter\" — dealt 30+ damage in one roll\n  - \"Lucky Seven\" — rolled exactly 7 three times\n  - \"Centurion\" — 100 total damage dealt\n  - \"Social Butterfly\" — used 5 different dice types in one session\n- Achievement unlocked: toast notification with badge icon + name\n- Achievement gallery: new section in character sheet showing all unlocked badges\n- Each badge: icon (emoji), name, description, date unlocked\n- WebSocket: broadcast achievement unlocks to all players (\"🏆 Richard unlocked: Natural Born!\")\n\n## Feature 3: Player Avatar Upload\nPlayers can upload an image as their character avatar.\n\n- In character sheet: \"📷 Upload Avatar\" button above character name\n- Click → file picker (jpg/png, max 500KB)\n- Image stored as data URL in character data (field: avatar)\n- Avatar displayed:\n  - Character sheet: circular, 80px, top of the sheet\n  - DM Party Overview: circular, 50px, in each player card\n  - Initiative tracker: small circular, 24px, next to name\n  - Battle Map tokens: use avatar image instead of solid color circle (if avatar exists)\n- Backend: accept avatar field in character save (already handles JSON, just add field)\n- Image resized client-side to max 200x200px before storing (canvas resize)\n\npm2 restart dnd-app when done."}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_KWen0TBnn1kawRXw61QWEW","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"agentId":"gabriel","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":600,"task":"Add these features to Paul Simulator (D&D web app). Read all existing files first.\n\n**Files:**\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/index.html\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/app.js\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/styles.css\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/backend/server.js\n\n## Feature 1: Character Journal\nPlayer-only feature. New section in character sheet or new tab.\n\n- Each player can write journal entries for their character (in-character diary)\n- Journal entry: {date, title, content, sessionNumber (optional)}\n- List of entries with newest first\n- \"Write Entry\" button → textarea + title input + save\n- \"🤖 AI Write Entry\" button:\n  - Takes recent session notes + dice roll history\n  - POST to backend → Council Room AI (sarael): \"Write a short in-character journal entry for [character name], a [species] [class]. Based on what happened: [session notes]. Write in first person, 100-200 words, in the character's voice.\"\n  - Player can edit before saving\n- Backend: store in character data (field: journal, array of entries)\n- GET /api/characters/:id/journal\n- POST /api/characters/:id/journal\n\n## Feature 2: Combat Simulator (DM only)\nDM can test encounter balance before the actual session.\n\n- New section or modal accessible from DM dashboard\n- Input: \n  - Party: auto-populate from room characters (level, HP, AC) or manual input (number of players, average level)\n  - Monsters: select from bestiary or manual input (name, CR, HP, AC, damage per round estimate)\n- Calculate encounter difficulty using D&D 2024 XP budget:\n  - Easy / Medium / Hard / Deadly based on party level vs total monster XP\n  - XP thresholds per character level (hardcode the table)\n- Show:\n  - Difficulty rating with color (green/yellow/orange/red)\n  - Estimated rounds to complete\n  - \"This encounter is DEADLY for your party\" or \"Your party should handle this easily\"\n  - Suggested adjustments (\"Add 2 more goblins for a Hard encounter\" or \"Remove 1 monster to make it Medium\")\n- AI analysis button: \"🤖 Analyze Encounter\" → AI gives tactical advice for the DM\n\n## Feature 3: Encounter Builder (DM only)\nExtends combat simulator into a full encounter builder.\n\n- DM picks monsters from bestiary → add to encounter\n- Running XP total + difficulty meter (bar that fills from Easy→Medium→Hard→Deadly)\n- Party info auto-loaded\n- \"Save Encounter\" → stored for later use\n- \"Start Encounter\" → adds all monsters to initiative tracker automatically\n- Backend: store encounters in /home/openclaw/dnd-app/data/encounters.json\n- GET/POST/DELETE /api/rooms/:pin/encounters\n\n## Feature 4: Character Relationship Map\nVisual graph showing character relationships.\n\n- New section accessible from Party Overview (DM) or as a shared tab\n- Simple graph visualization using SVG or Canvas:\n  - Nodes = characters (circle with name + avatar if exists)\n  - Edges = relationships (labeled lines)\n- DM can add relationships:\n  - Select two characters/NPCs\n  - Relationship type: ally, rival, romantic, mentor, enemy, family, business\n  - Custom label (optional)\n- Color-coded edges: ally=green, rival=orange, romantic=pink, mentor=blue, enemy=red, family=gold, business=gray\n- Interactive: click node to see character details\n- Backend: store in room data (field: relationships, array of {from, to, type, label})\n\npm2 restart dnd-app when done."}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_SESLEZ6zrgdWCqtL087W87","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"agentId":"rafael","mode":"run","runTimeoutSeconds":600,"task":"Add these features to Paul Simulator (D&D web app). Read all existing files first.\n\n**Files:**\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/index.html\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/app.js\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/frontend/styles.css\n- /home/openclaw/dnd-app/backend/server.js\n\n## Feature 1: AI Dungeon Master\nFull AI-powered DM mode for solo play or when no human DM is available.\n\n- New mode accessible from login screen: \"🤖 Solo Adventure (AI DM)\"\n- Creates a special room where AI is the DM\n- Flow:\n  1. Player creates/selects a character\n  2. AI sets the scene (generates opening narrative)\n  3. Player types what they want to do in a text input\n  4. AI responds with narrative + asks for dice rolls when needed\n  5. Combat: AI manages monsters, asks player to roll attacks/saves\n  6. AI tracks basic state: location, HP, inventory\n\n- Backend: POST /api/ai-dm/chat\n  Body: {characterData, conversationHistory (array of messages), playerAction}\n  Calls Council Room AI (sarael): \"You are a D&D 2024 Dungeon Master running a solo adventure. Character: [data]. Previous story: [history]. Player action: [action]. Respond with vivid narrative (2-4 paragraphs). If combat or skill check is needed, specify what roll is required (e.g., 'Roll a d20 + Dexterity for Stealth'). Track the story. Be dramatic and engaging. Include NPC dialogue in quotes.\"\n  Return: {narrative, rollRequired (null or {type, modifier, dc}), combatState (null or object)}\n\n- Frontend:\n  - Chat-style interface (like a text adventure)\n  - AI messages in a narrative font style (slightly different from player messages)\n  - When AI requests a roll → show integrated dice roller inline\n  - Player rolls → result sent back to AI → AI continues narrative\n  - \"Start New Adventure\" button with genre presets:\n    - 🏰 Classic Dungeon Crawl\n    - 🌲 Wilderness Exploration  \n    - 🏙️ Urban Mystery\n    - 🐉 Dragon Hunt\n    - 🎲 Random Adventure\n  - Save/load adventure state to localStorage\n\n- Conversation history kept in memory (array of {role: 'player'|'dm', text, roll})\n- Max 50 messages before summarizing older ones\n\n## Feature 2: Condition & Buff Tracker\nVisual tracker for all active effects on characters during combat.\n\n- In initiative tracker, each combatant can have active conditions/buffs\n- Add condition: dropdown with all D&D conditions + custom\n- Standard conditions: Blinded, Charmed, Deafened, Exhaustion (level 1-10), Frightened, Grappled, Incapacitated, Invisible, Paralyzed, Petrified, Poisoned, Prone, Restrained, Stunned, Unconscious\n- Custom buffs: Bless, Shield of Faith, Haste, Rage, Bardic Inspiration, Hex, Hunter's Mark, etc.\n- Each condition shows:\n  - Icon (emoji)\n  - Name\n  - Duration (rounds remaining, or concentration, or until long rest)\n  - Auto-decrement duration each round (when \"Next Turn\" is clicked)\n  - Visual warning when about to expire (1 round left)\n  - Auto-remove when expired\n- Conditions displayed as small colored pills below combatant name in initiative\n- Click pill → see details, remove, adjust duration\n- DM can add/remove conditions on any combatant\n- Players can add/remove on their own character\n- Concentration tracking: only one concentration effect at a time, warn if adding second\n\npm2 restart dnd-app when done."}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":2917,"cacheRead":388346,"cacheWrite":627,"totalTokens":391893,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.072925,"cacheRead":0.19417299999999998,"cacheWrite":0.00391875,"total":0.27103175}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774984133799}}
